  fiTitle: "Laurinm\xE4en torpparimuseo"
  fiPlace: Berttan salaisuus
  fiText: "Bertta kiirehti askeliaan V\xE4h\xE4-Kurjen torpan pihalla ja toivoi,
    ettei tulisi huomatuksi. Oli h\xE4nen h\xE4\xE4p\xE4iv\xE4ns\xE4 ja h\xE4n muuttaisi
    pysyv\xE4sti oman Aatunsa rinnalle. Molempia liittoja oli jo viikkokausia touhutettu
    ja anoppi-Maija oli ollut tyytyv\xE4inen h\xE4nen kapioihinsa. H\xE4\xE4t olisivat
    varsinainen tapaus, koska samalla vietett\xE4isiin my\xF6s torpan tytt\xE4ren
    h\xE4it\xE4. \r\n\r\nBerttalla oli kuitenkin yksi askare j\xE4ljell\xE4, jonka
    h\xE4n halusi ennen vihkimist\xE4 ehti\xE4. Iso\xE4iti oli opettanut, ett\xE4
    mets\xE4ss\xE4 olevan kiven kuppeihin piti tuoda lahjoja hyv\xE4n onnen takaamiseksi.
    Bertta kantoi mukanaan pient\xE4 pulloa, johon oli p\xE4\xE4tt\xE4nyt hakea ikiaikaisen
    l\xE4hteen vett\xE4 lahjaksi. \r\n\r\nNyky\xE4\xE4n sellaiseen eiv\xE4t tietenk\xE4\xE4n
    monet en\xE4\xE4 uskoneet, jotkut pelk\xE4siv\xE4tkin tai sanoivat niit\xE4 pakanoiden
    t\xF6iksi. Pelotti, ett\xE4 uusi anoppi muuttaisi suhtautumistaan, jos tiet\xE4isi.
    \r\n\r\nBerttan kumartuessa l\xE4hteelle t\xE4ytt\xE4m\xE4\xE4n pullonsa. Anoppi-Maija
    hymyili mets\xE4n reunassa tytt\xE4relleen \r\n\u201DKatsos vain mini\xE4\xE4,
    samalla asialla taidetaan olla.\u201D\r"
  enTitle: "Bertta\u2019s secret"
  enPlace: "Laurinm\xE4ki Crofter\u2019s Museum"
  enText: "Bertta hastened her steps outside the V\xE4h\xE4-Kurki house, wishing
    that she would go unnoticed. It was her wedding day, a day when she would move
    to live with her dear Aatu for good. Both marriages had been fussed over for
    weeks, and Maija, her future mother-in-law, was pleased with her trousseau. The
    wedding would be quite a special event, because the daughter of the house was
    also getting married. \r\n\r\nBertta still had something to take care of before
    the ceremony. Her grandmother had taught her to take offerings to the cups on
    a big rock in the forest for good luck. Bertta was carrying a small bottle. She
    had decided to get water from the ancient spring and take it as her offering.
    \r\n\r\nNot many people believed in these things anymore, and some were intimated
    and called them pagan worship. Bertta was scared that her new mother-in-law could
    also have second thoughts if she found out about this. \r\n\r\nAs Bertta was
    leaning over the spring to fill her bottle, Maija, her future mother-in-law,
    looked at the girl from the edge of the forest, smiled and thought to herself,
    \r\n\"Look at her, looks like we are on the same mission.\u201D\r"
